---
Name: Chih Kung
AlternateNames:
  - Chih-kung
Description: A Buddhist monk present in the court of the Emperor when
  Bodhidharma was presented. After Bodhidharma left, the emperor discussed
  the Indian with the monk, who expressed the possibility that Bodhidharma
  was a bodhisattva. When the emeror considered recalling him, Chih Kung
  disuaded the emperor.
---
